As a titanfall player this game is masterpiece and also a legend

I bought this game 2 years ago because I heard it had Lawrence of Arabia stuff in it, and he's one of my fave historical figures, but I'm terrible at FPS, was never really interested in war/military related video games, and didn't have the right graphics card to play at the time. But now I finally saved up enough to get a 3090 for gameplay/work, instead of jumping ahead to the Lawrence content I've been playing through all the other campaigns the past 2 days, and I'm blown away by how amazing this game is!! They really get to the heart and soul of the individual characters and it's honestly a masterpiece! That opening sequence where you're *expected* to die and you cycle through all those different soldiers and you see how long they lived will stick with me forever.

Plus, it's insanely fun to play - I mean, I'm only playing on easy for the story, but I can definitely see myself replaying this on harder difficulties because it controls so nicely! And every little part that I was nervous about (the in your face combat, the flying, etc) was really easy to pick up once I got over my nerves, and the fighting was overwhelming in a good way and it made me care so much about the characters. I've definitely cried at least a few times during these campaigns! I'm still a huge fan of T.E. Lawrence and can't wait to get to his content in this game,  but overall I'm just so impressed with Battlefield 1 and can't wait to play more games in this series. BF1 has definitely broadened my respect for those who served everywhere in WWI and made me enjoy history in a way I've never experienced before!
